ekiston Respublikasi Prezidentining 2020-yil 10-martdagi farmoni bilan Sardor Umurzoqov Ozbekiston Respublikasi Bosh vazirining investitsiyalar va tashqi iqtisodiy aloqalar masalalari boyicha orinbosari  Investitsiyalar va tashqi savdo vaziri etib tayinlandi.\r\nOzbekiston Respublikasi Prezidentining 2022-yil 16-iyuldagi farmoni bilan Sardor Umurzoqov Ozbekiston Respublikasi Prezidenti Administratsiyasi rahbari etib tayinlandi.\r\n\r\nShuningdek, 2019-yilning yanvaridan 2022-yilning 16-iyuliga qadar tashqi savdoni tarif va notarif tartibga solish boyicha kengash raisi hamda JSTga azo bolish boyicha idoralararo komissiya raisi bolgan.\r\n\r\n2019-yil avgustdan 2022-yil 16-iyulgacha  Tashqi savdo, investitsiyalar, sanoatni rivojlantirish va texnik jihatdan tartibga solish masalalari boyicha Hukumat komissiyasining raisi.\r\nShuningdek, 2022-yil 16-iyulgacha Ozbekiston Togridan-togri investitsiyalar jamgarmasi boshqaruvi raisi, Ozbekinvest AJ Kuzatuv kengashi raisi va Ozbekinvest xalqaro sugurta kompaniyasi direktorlar kengashi raisi (London, Buyuk Britaniya) lavozimlarida ishlagan. .\r\n\r\n2022-yilning 16-iyuliga qadar Yevropa tiklanish va taraqqiyot banki Boshqaruvchilar kengashi raisi orinbosari (shtab-kvartirasi London, Buyuk Britaniya).\r\n2022-yil 16-iyulgacha (shtab-kvartirasi  Pekin, Xitoy) Osiyo infratuzilma sarmoyalari banki boshqaruvchisi.\r\n\r\n2022-yil 16-iyulgacha Islom taraqqiyot banki Boshqaruvchilar kengashi raisi (Bosh qarorgohi  Jidda, Saudiya Arabistoni).\r\n2022-yil 16-iyulgacha Osiyo taraqqiyot banki gubernatori (shtab-kvartirasi  Manila, Filippin).\r\n\r\n2019-yil sentabridan  Ozbekiston Liberal-demokratik partiyasi Siyosiy Kengashi azosi\r\n\r\n2021-yil 11-dekabrdan  Ozbekiston Respublikasi Milliy tadqiqot universiteti Boshqaruv raisi.	Born in Tashkent on November 23, 1977. Father - Umurzakov Uktam Pardaevich (1952-2021), rector of the Tashkent Institute of Irrigation and Agricultural Mechanization Engineers - Chairman of the Council of Higher Education of the Republic of Uzbekistan. In the period from 1994 to 1998 he graduated from the Tashkent Perfect Univercity at the Faculty of International Finance and Banking. In 1998-1999 after receiving a bachelor's degree, he studied at the University of Reading (UK), where he received a master's degree in banking.\r\n\r\n2000-2003 - the beginning of labor activity in the banking sector at the National Bank for Foreign Economic Affairs of the Republic of Uzbekistan as a specialist of the 2nd category. Some time later, he became a 1st category specialist, then a leading specialist, and later, head of the investment management department. In 2003, he was appointed Deputy Governor of the Samarkand Department of the National Bank for Foreign Economic Affairs of the Republic of Uzbekistan.\r\n\r\nFrom 2004 to 2007 he lived in London, holding the position of a senior banker in the business group of financial institutions at the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. After returning from the UK, from 2007 to 2013. held senior positions in the Treasury of the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Uzbekistan: deputy head, then - head of the Treasury Department of the city of Tashkent and after - first deputy head of the Treasury of the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Uzbekistan.\r\n\r\nFrom 2014 to 2017 - Advisor to the Chairman of the Association "Uzbekcharmpoyabzali". Then (2017-2018) he worked as Deputy Chairman of the Board in the same Association. After, from 2018-2019. worked as chairman of the Uzcharmsanoat Association, created by reorganizing the Uzbekcharmpoyabzali Association.\r\n\r\nOn January 28, 2019, by the Decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan, Sardor Umurzakov was appointed Minister of Investments and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan.\r\nOn March 10, 2020, by the Decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan, Sardor Umurzakov was appointed Deputy Prime Minister for Investments and Foreign Economic Relations - Minister of Investments and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan\r\nOn July 16, 2022, by the Decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan, Sardor Umurzakov was appointed head of the Administration of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan.\r\n\r\nAlso, from January 2019 to July 16, 2022, he was Chairman of the Council on Tariff and Non-Tariff Regulation of Foreign Trade and Chairman of the Interdepartmental Commission for WTO Accession.\r\n\r\nFrom August 2019 to July 16, 2022 - Chairman of the Government Commission on Foreign Trade, Investment, Industrial Development and Technical Regulation.\r\nAlso, until July 16, 2022, he held the positions of Chairman of the Board of the Direct Investment Fund of Uzbekistan, Chairman of the Supervisory Board of Uzbekinvest JSC and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Uzbekinvest International Insurance Company (London, UK).\r\n\r\nVice Chairman of the Board of Governors of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development until 16 July 2022 (Headquarters London, UK).\r\nGovernor of the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank until July 16, 2022 (headquarters - Beijing, China).\r\n\r\nChairman of the Board of Governors of the Islamic Development Bank until July 16, 2022 (Headquarters - Jeddah, Saudi Arabia).\r\nGovernor of the Asian Development Bank until July 16, 2022 (headquarters - Manila, Philippines).\r\n\r\nSince September 2019 - Member of the Political Council of the Liberal Democratic Party of Uzbekistan\r\n\r\nSince December 11, 2021 - Chairman of the Governing Board of the National Research University of the Republic of Uzbekistan.	   23  1977 .  -    (1952-2021),          -      .    1994  1998            .  1998-1999          (),      .\r\n\r\n2000-2003                 2- .       1- ,   ,      .  2003            .\r\n\r\n 2004  2007    ,     -       .    ,  2007  2013 .         :  ,                  .\r\n\r\n 2014  2017      .  (2017-2018 )       . ,  2018-2019 .    ,     .\r\n\r\n28  20