2	2024-05-02 13:15:47.975818+00	2024-05-02 13:15:47.975829+00	1_science_description	IT, Software engineering	<p>It is not wrong to say that a person who has a strong knowledge of programming is a real independent person in today&#39;s information age. Because a programmer is a programmer in Africa, China, and America. Its platform is a personal computer, and its language is a programming language. A Chinese farmer and a London professor can understand and use the product that makes it. Today, programmers use more than ten programming languages. In 2017, the Java programming language was considered one of the 3 most used languages. In terms of scope and coverage, this language occupies the largest part of the information field. It is possible to write programs for almost all techniques and systems in this language.<br />\r\nTherefore, the Java programming language is a universal language. With its help, you can create and produce everything from web applications to mobile, computer and additional electronic devices and devices. Why is Java universal? Everything is in its &quot;virtual machine&quot; - this component adapts the written codes to any equipment, device or operating system.</p>	2
3	2024-05-02 13:15:47.976725+00	2024-05-02 13:15:47.976735+00	2_purpose_of_science	IT, Software engineering	<p>The purpose of teaching the subject is to provide students with theoretical knowledge of software design and development, to introduce Java interface innovations, to use modern programming languages to develop and test software tools, and to create web applications that are popular today. consists of forming practical skills.<br />\r\nThe task of the subject is to teach the students within the scope of the subject, i.e. Java operators, conditional, comparison and loop operators in Java, working with arrays in Java, Java String, converting data from one type to another type in Java, object-oriented programming (OOP ) 1, (OOP) 2 and performs tasks such as formation of theoretical knowledge and practical skills in working with Java libraries</p>	2
